    <h1>Pick lists</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, you can generate pick lists as PDF or CSV files, for example if you want to print them or import them into another software. You can display barcodes on your pick lists. These allow you to scan items directly and book outgoing items after completion of the picking process.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Displaying item data</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the menu <strong>Setup » Orders » Documents » Pick list</strong> to determine which item data should be displayed on your pick lists, such as <strong>Item ID</strong>, <strong>Manufacturers</strong> or <strong>Item price</strong>.<br></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can carry out individual settings for most of the fields described in <a href="#table-orders-options-pick-list">[table-orders-options-pick-list]</a> concerning the parameters <strong>width</strong>, font size and font weight that allow you to individualise the layout of the warehouse pick list. Use the <strong>Preview</strong> (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-eye  "></i></span>) to check the results of the settings while preparing the PDF template.
To display the fields on the pick list in the order of your choice, assign the position numbers 1 to 14 from the respective drop-down list to them. Select the option <strong>Pos</strong> for fields that should not be displayed on the pick list.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Displaying item data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Documents » Pick list</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information provided in <a href="#table-orders-options-pick-list">[table-orders-options-pick-list]</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-options-pick-list" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
<caption class="title">Table 1. Options in the <strong>Pick list</strong> menu</caption>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 25%;">
